    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for April 13th is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29), who stands as our clear elite play today. Facing Ryne Nelson, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a 16% park boost and favorable winds, combined with a projected leadoff spot that maximizes his plate appearance volume. **Kyle Tucker** (72.71) and **Josh Lowe** (66.40) follow closely as top-tier outfield options; while **Kyle Tucker** provides stable xwOBA production against David Peterson, **Josh Lowe** is a priority start despite a lower lineup position due to a significant platoon advantage against Will Warren and the high-scoring potential of today's wind conditions. **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.22) also earns a high score; his matchup against the relatively soft Justin Wrobleski is bolstered by an 85% stolen base success rate projection against the pitcher\u2019s delivery, making him a critical weapon in our chase for the league's scarcest category.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved leaving **Marcell Ozuna** (52.88) on the bench. While he offers reliable power, he was narrowly edged out by **Nolan Schanuel** (58.19), whose floor against Will Warren proved more attractive to the optimizer for filling the UTIL slot. Meanwhile, **Josh Jung** (60.22) managed to crack the starting lineup primarily due to an favorable 15% SP skill adjustment against Luis Severino\u2019s shaky xERA. We must remain cautious of the \"Lineup Pending\" status for players like **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks**; should these projections fluctuate, we risk diminished R and RBI production if they are dropped in the order. Additionally, while **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** possesses a solid 53.78 score, facing Paul Skenes represents our most significant SP skill risk of the day, forcing us to temper expectations for the middle infield despite his platoon advantage.",
